TopicTitle: Incompatiblity between KSPI-E, NFE and MKS/UKS

Articles.Content:
Hello

I have a problem with my heavily modded KSP 1.1.3 install. But i managed to pin down the conflicting mods with a clean install

USI Kolonization Systems (MKS/OKS) 0.40.4 - Near Future Electrical 0.7.5 & KSP Interstellar Extended 1.9.2

Any 2 of these work perfectly fine together, but putting these 3 together results in the game to hang up on part loading "UmbraSpaceIndustries/ReactorPack/Parts/Nuke_125/USI_Nuke_125" - at about 90% of the loading sequence.

 

So my exact set of Addons is:

Quote

Module manager 2.6.25 - 000_Toolbar - 000_FilterExtensions - 000_FilterExtensions Configs - 000_USITools - CommunityResourcePack - Firespitter - InterstellarFuelSwitch - NearFutureElectrical - RcsSounds - TweakScale - UmbraSpaceIndustries - WarpPlugin

This is my log

If you have NFE installed and deleted the USI balance file everything should be fine without the need to fix anything.
